      "author": "christian-luger-at",
      "description": "Focus First 1.5.0 turns the matrix into a flexible prioritisation workspace: a second Value/Effort matrix, task sizes, quick-wins filtering, and a today-plan focus list.\n\n### Features\n- **Value/Effort matrix** — switch the 2×2 between Eisenhower (urgency × importance) and Value/Effort (Quick Wins / Big Bets / Fill-ins / Time Sinks) from a compact header dropdown. Value comes from priority or a `#highvalue`/`#lowvalue` tag; effort from task size. Drag tasks between quadrants to re-classify. (#36)\n- **Task size** — mark tasks small / medium / large with configurable tags (`#s`/`#m`/`#l`) straight from the detail popover. (#35)\n- **Size filter & quick wins** — narrow the matrix by task size in the search area; \"Small\" is your quick-wins lens. (#30)\n- **Today-plan focus list** — the Focus section is now an ordered, numbered shortlist; drag to reorder (persisted) with an optional daily-target line. (#34, #37)\n- **Undo toast** — complete, hide, move, re-prioritise, and drag-and-drop each show a brief Undo. (#32)\n- **Streamlined search** — opening search reveals all filters at once; the separate \"More Filters\" toggle is gone. (#29)\n\n### Fixes\n- Focus tasks never show the \"why here\" reason, regardless of the setting. (#31)\n- Focus reorder: the first and last positions are now reachable. (#37)\n\n### Other\n- Axis selector refined into a compact header dropdown.\n- Contributor demo-vault generator (`scripts/gen-demo-vault.mjs`).",
